bio.experienceSummary:
Hi families! My name is Edreasha and I have 11 years of childcare experience. I am a registered nurse, author and therapist in training. I love children and I have always wanted to have a career that would allow me the opportunity to make a difference in children's lives. My "Sitting" style can be described as Professional, Reliable, and Fun! I am a true believer in positive reinforcement and team work. Therefore, I make it important to have open dialogue with not only the child(ren) involved, but the parents as well. We're all in this together and although this is a job to me, I would love to become part of your family also. 

My hobbies are: Cooking, (I can make just about anything.) Writing, and yoga. 

I hope to have the opportunity to work with your family and make a difference in your children's lives.

description.originalText: Edreasha is really great! She is kind and trustworthy. She regularly comes and cares for our 11 months old twins and 6 year old girl. They all love her. And she does a great job keeping us updated throughout the evening, when we’re out.

bio.experienceSummary: I have been working with children since I was 16 (longer if you count that I am the oldest of five siblings!). I have 8 years of professional experience as a caretaker and educator. I worked at Stanford's Bing Nursery School teaching 2-5-year-olds with an emphasis on social emotional learning and children-led curriculum. I have worked as a live-in nanny and live-in pre-school teacher for infants and children ages 1-7. During college, I worked as a camp counselor for three summers with 5-18-year-olds, I led a summer curriculum program for 7-18-year-olds, I lived in Ecuador creating and implementing programming for 6-18-year-olds, I taught a dance summer camp for three years, and I babysat consistently. I speak Spanish fluently and am very passionate about the arts. My focus with children is rooted in assumed competence frameworks, an emphasis on social-emotional learning, and is tailored to the children and parent's needs. Excited to meet you

I'm a passionate caregiver with a genuine love for nurturing the growth and development of young minds. My journey into childcare began with fulfilling babysitting experiences that ignited my desire to make a positive impact on children's lives.

As a patient, creative, and friendly individual, I strive to create a safe and stimulating environment for children to learn, play, and thrive. I prioritize open communication with parents, ensuring that I understand their preferences and concerns. With a firm belief in consistency, I'm very comfortable enforcing household rules to maintain a structured and harmonious environment.

With six years of experience, I relish engaging children in a variety of activities that cater to their interests and age groups. From outdoor adventures and physical games to board games and educational experiences, I aim to foster their physical, cognitive, and emotional development.

Hello! My name is Devon, and I am excited to offer my babysitting and nannying services. With extensive experience at a cooperative daycare focused on children aged 3-10, I am well-equipped to handle various childcare needs, ensuring a safe and engaging environment for your children.

I have also tutored elementary and middle school children in English literature, helping them improve their reading and writing skills. Currently, I am exploring programs to pursue a career as a child psychologist, driven by my passion for early childhood development and creating screen-free, creative environments.

I hold a Bachelor's Degree in American Studies & English Literature from The George Washington University and have a professional background as a Director of Marketing and Sales Strategy. I am available for both short-term and long-term positions, aiming to build meaningful relationships with families and provide consistent, reliable care.

My name is Lauren, and I'm a Brooklyn-based Nanny/Household Assistant! :) 

As the oldest in my family, I've always been around little ones and childcare has always been one of my greatest joys. Over the last decade I've had countless childcare jobs, whether it be as a live-in for families of multiples, for families with infants, managing the Performing Arts department of a summer camp with up to 600 kids ages 7 to 16, tutoring and caring for children with Autism and Williams Syndrome, directing children in plays and musicals, accompanying families to weddings/special events, the list goes on! Additionally, I have specialized experience with children who have experienced grief, and have assisted with remote learning. 

I'm fully vaccinated, welcome housework, and am comfortable with travel. Currently, I'm looking for Full-Time work with one family.

I love learning more about the world through kids, engaging them in play, and just being an asset to a family however I can. :)

Hi! I'm Nicole - please PM with any questions. 
Currently (Jan 2025), I am available for all services listed below on weekends & occasional evenings. (no weekday daytime. Beginning July 2025, I will also have available Monday and Friday 7:30AM-3 p.m.  In September 2025, I will additionally have Tuesdays open as well. 
 
Services: 
adhoc childcare, event childcare, organizational help, house management, and meal prep services!

description.originalText: Nicole is incredibly reliable, honest and genuinely cares about the kids she watches. She’s been with us for 3 years and she treats my boys like her own kids. She is very flexible and is willing to do activities, park- whatever to make it fun for them!

bio.experienceSummary: I have been working as a nanny for over 20 years now both in Manhattan and Queens area. I have excellent references. I worked with twins, new borns, toddlers and younger children. I am now looking for a new family who I can support and provide the best service. If anyone looking for an amazing nanny, feel free to message me. Thank you.

Hello! My name is Clair (I go by my middle name) and I have been baby-sitting and nannying for children of all ages from infants-12 years old for 10+ years. I have experience working in a preschool with 3-5-year-olds and in a daycare with 1-5-year-olds. I am currently completing my last semester of Physical Therapy School at Primary Children's Hospital and am infant and child CPR and AED certified. I love crafts, playing outside, and reading with kids. I can help with Travel, Swimming Supervision, online class, and more. I am high energy and love working with kids and helping them learn and grow!

description.displayText: Anna was open and friendly from the moment she walked through our door. I have two kids that she watched, one being an 8 month old that only likes "mom" and I was a little nervous about. She handled everything like grace, and made me feel very comfortable leaving two little girls in her care. One of the best experiences I've had with care.com!

bio.experienceSummary:
I am an experienced nanny of 11 years with a BA in Art Education and a strong understanding of child development. I have worked with children of all ages, from infants to early teens, with my most recent experience being with two elementary-aged children on the autism spectrum. I am warm, patient, and deeply committed to nurturing a child's physical, mental, and emotional growth and am continuously expanding my knowledge of child development.

I believe in fostering creativity and learning through play, incorporating arts and crafts, imaginative activities, and hands-on exploration into daily routines. I also love spending time outdoors and engaging in the community. 

I have extensive experience assisting with household tasks, including cooking, cleaning, laundry, and running errands. I am open to more creative chores as well; the way I see it it's my job to assist you as a parent and make your life easier.

description.displayText: Lizzie babysat for us just once and on very short notice and we would have her again in a second! She was on time, and I could instantly tell that my son liked her. Children are the best judges and you can easily tell by their reactions when someone is a good caregiver or not and Lizzie definitely is!

bio.experienceSummary:
I was an EMT of NY State and got paramedic training.
IBLS (Basic Life Support). Paramedic certificate, I worked as a paramedic 2015 to 2017.
I worked at a daycare , where I was the main teacher for 2-4 yo children, teaching the kids the numbers, alphabet, vocabulary, nursery songs, courtesy habits, sphincter control and reinforcing values. 
I also babysit kids from newborn-10 years old, helping them with homework, meal preparation and outdoor activities. 
I have 8+ years of experience with children.
Volunteered Children Minister in Church.
About myself I love reading, dancing, singing and I enjoy outdoors activities. I believe that the greatest value is the honesty. I had been raised in a Christian family. I love pets. And I consider myself as a responsible person.
English and Spanish (native) speaker, basic Arabic.
Fully vaxx
